\n< Tim >Ah, h-how was it?

\n< Serena >There were a few books in my study that I had
never seen before.
\n< Serena >I would like to request a reservation, but...

\n< Tim >I'll do it! I'll make a reservation! Which one is
it!? I'll keep it securely!

\n< Serena >N-No, I can't do that. Because of my unstable
situation right now, I don't know when I'll be
able to come and buy it.

\n< Serena >Well then, it would be a bother for the store.
Once my personal situation has settled down, I
will come again at that time to make a
reservation.
\n< Tim >I see...

\n< Tim >But, that's amazing. To have two or three books
that you've never seen before, that means you have
a study that rivals our library, right?
\n< Serena >Yes... ah...
\n< Tim >？

\n< Serena >Oh no... Lord Tim, I have a secret request about
what just happened.
\n< Tim >That? Are you talking about the reservation?
\n< Serena >No, it's about the books in the library...

\n< Tim >......Ah, ah... That's right. Now that I think
about it, just how many expensive books do you
personally own...
\n< Serena >Lord Tim.
\n< Tim >Ah, s-sorry. But there's no one else here...

\n< Serena >Even so, I apologize for involving you in my slip
of the tongue...

\n< Tim >Ahaha. It's okay. I'll sew my mouth shut. I won't
let those words slip out again.

\n< Serena >Thank you... There's a slightly special
circumstance...
\n< Tim >U-Understood... But, then, this, is it about that?
\n< Serena >？
\n< Tim >It's about the two of us, our secret, right?
\n< Serena >Hmm... Well, let's go with that.
\n< Tim >E-eh, ehe, ehehe.
\n< Serena >？
\n< Tim >S-Sorry. My face, it's smirking...
\n< Tim >Sorry, I'll go make some tea real quick!

\n< Serena >No, I can't stay for long. I have to go home
now...
\n< Serena >Hmm.

\n< Barden >Oh.

\n< Barden >Oh?

\n< Serena >Excuse me, but the store attendant is away from

there's probably nothing else besides coming to

\n< Tim >Umm...

\n< Serena >If I have time again, I'll stop by.

\n< Serena >.......

\n< Serena >Hello.
\n< Serena >Excuse me, shopkeeper.
\n< Boy >...Ah, ha-ha! Oh, a customer... I'm sorry!

\n< Serena >Excuse me, shopkeeper. I would like to sell a
book.

\n< Boy >Ah, s-sorry. I-I'm not the shopkeeper, just a shop
assistant...
\n< Serena >Hm? Is that so? Then, where is the shopkeeper...

\n< Boy >The shopkeeper is out on a buying trip and won't
be back for a while...
\n< Serena >Is that so... Mmm...

\n< Boy >Ah, are you looking to sell something? If it's
something listed in our catalog, I can give you a
price...
\n< Serena >Is that so? It's about this book...

\n< Boy >Wow, the original... um, the title is... Freedom
of Natural Instinct... I think?
\n< Serena >The original is only the cover.

\n< Boy >Ah, that's right... the writing inside is
amazing...
\n< Serena >I wonder if it's difficult to buy this book?

\n< Boy >No, this is pretty normal. It's actually quite
rare to find a brand new book...

\n< Boy >Hmm... I'm sorry, but it seems like this book
isn't listed in our catalog...

\n< Boy >I think if the shopkeeper were here, they could
have given you a price...

\n< Serena >I see... Well, I wasn't expecting much anyway. If
you can't buy it, then you can't. That's fine.
\n< Boy >You seem a little happy.
\n< Serena >N-No, it's not like that.
\n< Boy >Do you like books?

\n< Serena >Ah, books are great. They nourish the brain. A
good book is similar to a good meal.

\n< Boy >Ehehe, you say nice things. My theory is that
books are edible too.

\n< Serena >We seem to get along well. I'm Serena, an
adventurer.
\n< Tim >Oh, well, well. I am Tim.

\n< Tim >I'm also an adventurer, for the record. I'm not
very good at fighting, so I mostly take on
miscellaneous tasks like this...

\n< Serena >Is that so? Then we might have unknowingly crossed
paths at the guild.

\n< Tim >Well, I'm not sure about that. I'm not good with
the atmosphere there... so I try to avoid going
there as much as possible...

\n< Serena >Hehe, I feel the same way. The atmosphere there is
not good. First of all, the air is bad. And
there's no natural light either.
\n< Tim >It feels like the adult world, doesn't it?

\n< Serena >I'm such a bad adult... Ah, I ended up talking
about something pointless.

\n< Serena >I apologize, but I must hurry. It was fun talking,
but I can't stay and chat too long.

\n< Tim >Is that so? With a big belly, it must be, um,
really tough...
\n< Serena >Well... I guess so...

\n< Tim >Um, if it's okay with you, please come again.
Pregnant people can't move around much, right? I
think books or something would definitely be
helpful to you.
\n< Tim >Is that so? That's too bad.

\n< Tim >If it's okay with you, please come again. The
store manager won't be back for a while, but we
change the books every day...

\n< Tim >If you love books, I think you'll enjoy this
store... um, I believe so...
\n< Serena >Yes. If I have time, I'll come by again.
\n< Serena >Well then, Lord Tim. I must take my leave.
\n< Tim >Phew... I got startled.

\n< Tim >She's such a cute girl. Her eyes are as red as
rubies.
\n< Tim >Serena-chan...
\n< Tim >I wonder if she'll come again...

\n< Serena >Well then, it's about time to return to the
brothel. I wonder what kind of new job it will
be...
